    {
      "name": "AUTL",
      "description": "Authorization list",
      "help": "Authorization list (AUTL)\n\nSpecifies the authorization list whose entries are to be used to grant authority for the object specified. You must have authorization list management (*AUTLMGT) authority for the specified authorization list.\n\nIf a value is specified for this parameter, you cannot specify a value for the AUT, REFOBJ, or REFOBJTYPE parameters.\n\n指定できる特殊値: *NONE",
      "inputType": "text",
      "required": false,
      "attributes": {
        "characterSet": "upper",
        "maxLength": 10
      },
      "placeholder": "*NONE",
      "basic": true
    },
    {
      "name": "REFOBJ",
      "description": "Reference object",
      "help": "Reference object (REFOBJ)\n\nSpecifies the reference object to be queried to obtain authorization information. Those authorizations are given to the object specified by the OBJ and OBJTYPE parameters. Users authorized to the reference object are authorized in the same manner to the object for which authority is to be given. Database row and column access control masks and permissions will not be changed. If the reference object is secured by an authorization list, that authorization list secures the object specified by the OBJ and OBJTYPE parameters.\n\nIf a value is specified for this parameter, you cannot specify a value for the AUT or AUTL parameters.\n\nQualifier 2: Library",
      "inputType": "group",
      "required": false,
      "groupKind": "qualified",
      "children": [
